# Admin Data Grid

`AppDataGrid` is a shared admin table primitive. Keep it outside feature slices.

## Responsibilities

- `AppDataGrid` owns table UI state: page, page size, search input, debounced search, filters, sorting, column visibility, loading, empty, and error states.
- Feature/list pages own columns, feature-specific filters, toolbar actions, and the SDK client fetcher.
- Do not move the grid into a feature folder. Products, categories, and tax classes all reuse the same grid pattern.

## Fetchers

- Grid fetchers should call raw SDK list clients and adapt the response to `{ data, meta }`.
- Cast grid sort/filter values to the generated SDK query param enum types at the page boundary.
- Include every query-shaping parameter in the grid query key by passing `queryKey` plus grid `params`.

## Cache Keys

- Pass a resource query-key prefix from the feature hook module, preferably from generated SDK key helpers.
- Mutations should invalidate the same prefix so grid queries refresh with detail and option queries.

## UI

- Keep generic toolbar, pagination, search, filter, and column visibility behavior in `components/app-data-grid`.
- Keep feature-specific cell formatting in the page or a feature-owned helper.
